  "commentary": "With SPX at 6822.93 sitting just below the max positive gamma strike at 6825, dealers are likely selling into any further upside push as they're long gamma and need to hedge by selling rallies. The thick wall of positive gamma from 6825-6900 creates a strong ceiling that should cap upside momentum and promote mean reversion back toward the 6797 flip level. Watch for resistance at 6825-6830 where combined +11B in GEX will trigger heavy dealer selling, while any dip toward 6797 flip should see stabilizing buying interest.\n\nBottom line: expect sideways chop with upside capped around 6825 and support near 6800.",
